OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1779134802
OL,3,CCelebrations for the Irish cattle
OL,4,Cwhich saw off possible extinction
OL,6,FFollowing the judging, breeders
OL,7,Fenjoyed a selection of Irish Moiled
OL,8,Fbeef burgers, sausages and brisket.
OL,10,FWhat is the Irish Moiled breed?
OL,12,FThe name of the breed comes from the
OL,13,FGaelic word 'maol' meaning hornless.
OL,14,F'Moil' is the anglicised form of the
OL,15,FGaelic word that is used by the breed
OL,16,Fsociety.
OL,18,FIrish Moiled cattle were most numerous
OL,19,Fin counties Tyrone, Armagh, Donegal
OL,20,Fand Sligo during the early 1900's.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1779134802
OL,3,CCelebrations for the Irish cattle
OL,4,Cwhich saw off possible extinction
OL,6,FPioneering breeders were interrupted
OL,7,Fdue to war and it was not until 1926
OL,8,Fthat a society was started in Belfast.
OL,10,FThere were strong classes at the Royal
OL,11,FUlster Agricultural Show at Balmoral
OL,12,Fin the 1920's and 1930's.
OL,14,FHowever, in the 1950's the society
OL,15,Fbegan to decline, before it's revival
OL,16,Fin 1982 when an effort was made to
OL,17,Fconserve the breed.
OL,19,FThere were only around 20 females and
OL,20,Ftwo bulls surviving.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G11/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1779134802
OL,3,CCelebrations for the Irish cattle
OL,4,Cwhich saw off possible extinction
OL,6,FBy 1984, calves were being registered
OL,7,Fagain with the aim of the society to
OL,8,Fhave a great entry of Irish Moiled
OL,9,Fcattle at the show once again.
OL,11,FIrish Moiled cattle had greatly
OL,12,Fincreased in numbers by 2010, but the
OL,13,Fbreed was still listed under the RBST
OL,14,Flist as 'at risk'.
OL,16,FAfter 80 years of missing the breed's
OL,17,Fpresence in the show ring, 2013 saw
OL,18,Fcompetitive Irish Moiled classes back
OL,19,Fat the Balmoral Show.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G12/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,448,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F447A1779134802
OL,3,CCelebrations for the Irish cattle
OL,4,Cwhich saw off possible extinction
OL,6,FIn 2024, it was a record-breaking year
OL,7,Ffor the breed with over 300 female
OL,8,Fregistrations in a single year.
OL,10,FBalmoral Show 2026
OL,12,FThe 157th Balmoral Show at the Eikon
OL,13,FExhibition Centre near Lisburn runs
OL,14,Funtil Saturday. It is deemed as
OL,15,FNorthern Ireland's premier
OL,16,Fagricultural event.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/15
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
